section.section:
A person may not commit an assault with a firearm, including:
a handgun, antique firearm, rifle, shotgun, short-barreled shotgun, or short-barreled rifle, as those terms are defined in § 4-201 of this article;
an assault pistol, as defined in § 4-301 of this article;
a machine gun, as defined in § 4-401 of this article; and
a regulated firearm, as defined in § 5-101 of the Public Safety Article.
